{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r742544115", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Not as good as it used to be", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "2 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Lucy O", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "5"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r742544115-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["We visited last night with friends for the 7 course tasting menu after being bowled over by a previous visit but unfortunately we were left a little disappointed. ", "The food in itself was very good (the stone bass was a particular hit) but having booked the 7 course tasting through Virgin I was disappointed to see that it was really 6 courses with small add ons (amuse Bouche & petit fours) with the cheese course charged at an additional \u00a315. This was not the case last year and certainly an unwelcome surprise as this was not made clear at any stage. ", "We also opted for the wine pairing at \u00a360 per person and whereas previously the excellent sommelier Olga had talked us through the wines with tasting notes, in this case we were forced to ask what each wine was (in one case the waiter was MIA so we still have no idea) and the pairing wine for dessert was actually served after we had finished. ", "A large party arrived to eat in the private dining room mid way through our meal and this made the initially attentive team somewhat elusive. ", "Really unfortunate as it was something special but beginning to understand why there never seems to be more than 4 or 5 tables occupied as once. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r745286155", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Perfect \ud83d\udc4c\ud83c\udffb", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "15 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Anto144", "reviewer_origin": ["Piacenza, Italy"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "18"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "13"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r745286155-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["my experience at the peninsula surely exceeded our expectations", "it was already recommended to us by our friends that they had had a great time ", "We chose a tasting menu with wine pairings, all excellent and cared for, and the superb , attentive and highly professional service made our dinner perfect.", "Every detail is taken care of, and as customers it feels unique", "thanks, we will be back"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r746267548", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Sublime dinner from the starter all the way through dessert", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "20 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "cybersecurityUK", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r746267548-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["I had the pleasure to visit the Peninsula restaurant for a work dinner last night. The restaurant is located on the top of the the hotel lobby, in a very luxurious setting whose charming atmosphere was enhanced by the spectacular view of Canary Wharf. I was recommended to got for the tasting menu by a member of staff who was very knowledgeable and made us feel at ease and comfortable at all times. When I asked for the wine, the waiter called over the Manager who was able to suggest and thoroughly explain the best options that would go very well with the food and that would meet our palate.", "Regarding the food, the beef was beautifully done accompanied by a life-changing Bearnaise sauce. The dessert was superb and well thought-through, the ice cream on top had an infrequent but surprisingly nice greeny taste. its also worth mentioning the espresso i finished off with which was excellent. ", "The staff was very nice and professional and managed to meet our requests and expectations. ", "Definitely a Michelin-starred level restaurant. I am pretty sure they will get one in the soon, Keep up the good work!!", "Overall a 5 star experience."]}
