{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r537753235", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Nice try but no thanks: average on all levels", "diner_date": " November 2017", "rating_date": "1 November 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "busterken", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "105"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "47"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r537753235-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["This place has a nice view and basic European service and may thus please an overseas population, but trust me this is not worth the money or the tour. The service is below all levels for the kind of place they pretend to be: not personal, many errors and no love. The food has even less love. Tastes like your typical big party overpaid caterer. Take my word on this: it might be worth a visit if you have the cash and happen to stay in the hotel, else stay away. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r539350466", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Always superb food", "diner_date": " October 2017", "rating_date": "8 November 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "777bent", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "5"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r539350466-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["We've eaten here a few times now - always the tasting menus, which are superb. They've been happy to help with substitutions (mixing the two menus for a non-seafood-eater), but I would actually recommend the vegetarian tasting menu above anything else.", "Each dish has great flavours and textures and introduces you to something entirely new. The gnocchi in particular is unbeatable.", "For a hotel-restaurant, in a modern chain hotel, this will exceed all expectations. It's also probably the best restaurant in south-east london. Maybe not up there with the Michelin stars of the west end, but the price (\u00a360 for 7 courses, compared to 100+ at those places) reflects this."]}
