{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r538710696", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "visit to the o2 Arena", "diner_date": " November 2017", "rating_date": "6 November 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Nick366", "reviewer_origin": ["Chelmsford"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "29"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "19"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r538710696-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["1st time we have visited this restaurant arrived at 1730 ,I chose from set menu as this is what I was going to have", "from the A La Carte menu which my wife chose from. The service from the Maitre d and all the staff was excellent they could not be more helpful, I would rate the meal we had as one of the best. We left at around 1930hrs to see the show we were not rushed at all. There is also a bar on the 18th floor that has excellent views over looking the Thames, we will definitely be going back"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r538971310", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Brilliant food ", "diner_date": " November 2017", "rating_date": "7 November 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "paptan1", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "104"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "46"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r538971310-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["We visited the Peninsula restaurant for my birthday. It is located in the Inter Continental hotel by O2 in North Greenwich. ", "The decor is a bit old style and the feel/service is formal. The views are fantastic but they need to work out the lighting so that it does not spoil the views.", "The service was formal, attentive but a bit forgetful. They forgot it was my birthday even though my wife had reminded them a few times. Apart from that it was brilliant- they were super knowledgeable, lovely to chat with, attentive without being overbearing.", "The food is the highlight. We chose the 7 course menu. My wife is pescatarian and they combined the options from the menus for her. the plating is lovely - good playing always cheers me up. The tastes are flavourful. I really liked the partridge, halibut and the beef; while my wife loved the butternut squash, Gnocchi and the halibut. The deserts were again beautifully presented."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r538577460", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Extremely disappointing", "diner_date": " October 2017", "rating_date": "5 November 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Peter A", "reviewer_origin": ["Faversham, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "3"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r538577460-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["Dreadful Muzak played, little atmosphere. We had the tasting menu which we were really looking forward to.unfortunately we both found the food to be a mixture of too many flavours resulting in it being unclear as to what we were eating. Service was satisfactory."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r539080177", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great views and the food was superb", "diner_date": " November 2017", "rating_date": "7 November 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "RichardAJohn", "reviewer_origin": ["Esher, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "87"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "30"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "40", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r539080177-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["We had not expected amazing things at this restaurant, however had we done our research we would have realised that this was a potential treat. And so it turned out. The service was very friendly, although could be a little over-eager sometimes. The views were outstanding, although the best views were for tables for 2 and there were three of us. The food was outstanding and earns the 5* review. All of our dishes were excellent and we would have no hesitation in going back should we ever visit the O2."]}
