{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r521340342", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Birthday Celebration", "diner_date": " August 2017", "rating_date": "5 September 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "oanaandrei2017", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r521340342-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["Very good, nice and warm atmosphere, staff very helpful, trying to accomodate us with all the requests. Nice food, we recommend the 7 course menu, lots of variation. We loved that even if it was short notice, at the end of the dinner the staff made a wonderful surprise to my mother which celebrated her 70th birthday with a nice cake & candle lights.", "Wonderfull view over the river and quiet location for a nice family dinner."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r523501227", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Evening meal at the Intercotinental Hotel at the O2", "diner_date": " August 2017", "rating_date": "11 September 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Tony B", "reviewer_origin": ["Romford, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "6"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "4"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r523501227-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["Lovely setting, overlooking the Thames and Canary Wharf.", "Beautiful meal. We had originally got the meal as a deal through Groupon at \u00a349.00 for two, but of course expected the usual selection of wines to be medium priced. (\u00a346.00), That along with extras for our limited choice within the fixed menu, but certainly enough choices. And of course the discretionary 12.5% service charge brought our final bill to around \u00a3116.00.", "I should imagine using the A La Carte menu, a decent bottle of wine and no holds (Cocktails, spirits and coffees), you could easily spend \u00a3200-300 for two of you.", "But how often do you spoil yourself?", "The staff were very friendly, courteous and helpful. With offers from the wine waiter to help with your choice. Overall a very unhurried and pleasant evening and experience.", "Please be aware though: if travelling by public transport (we did because we did other things like the Emirates cable car ride, close by - plus we wanted a chilled evening being able to enjoy a couple of glasses). The entrance is to the Hotel can only be gained by walking to the left of the O2 complex. We were told just to follow all the signs through the O2 and out the other side, which is exactly what we did. This only led to new construction there which is quite extensive, and a locked gate - then an even longer walk all the way back and around the O2 with sore feet.", "I gave it an excellent review, because we are talking about the meal and Hotel. It was just unfortunate about the directions and the fact the O2 itself have not covered the directions throughout the complex, whilst the works are continuing. If you are driving, check out with reception for parking. There is quite a large car park - obviously for residents."]}
