{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r518075180", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Reminded us of a top restaurant on a Cunard cruise ship", "diner_date": " August 2017", "rating_date": "27 August 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Martin J", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "9"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "6"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r518075180-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["Fantastic dinner at Peninsula restaurant last night. Hugely impressive hotel with restaurant on the 2nd floor. When we arrived our table wasn't quite ready so they asked if we'd mind going to the bar for 5 minutes. We went up to the bar on 18th floor and were really pleased we had; amazing views, great service and not too busy for 8.30pm on a Saturday night.", "When we returned to the restaurant for dinner we were seated at a window seat overlooking Canary Wharf. We opted for the tasting menu with paired wines. The food and wine was fantastic, supported by lovely friendly and professional service. The restaurant only seats around 40 but is very spacious. ", "Our favourite courses were the Panna Cotta, the cod, and the quail and peas. ", "We will definitely be back and will try the vegetarian tasting menu next time. ", "\u00a3325 for two people is far from cheap, but it was a real highlight and treat. Thank you Csaba and team. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r517755954", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "A work of art to the eye and pallet!", "diner_date": " August 2017", "rating_date": "26 August 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Eatingwithkiki", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "35"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "36"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r517755954-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["My friend and I went on a weekday as a summer treat, adn trust me it was. We both chose the tasting menu after a long reflection, as too many items on the menu looked appealling. We then ask the lovely waitress if we were able to have something swapped from the tasting menu Which the chef gladly accepted.", "We began with some amuse bouches, a 7 course with a variety of local seasonal produce, from cornish crab to quail, and all presented so delicately and beautifully that we would simply be glad to stare like a piece of art, but then we were hungry... So the next step was enjoying the different textures and making our taste buds smile while holding back on stuffing it all too fast!", "The highlights:", "The cornish crab ", "The quail!!! Most tender quail I have ever had in my life! ", "The pallet cleanser, a nice sorbet with little pieces of meringue.", "To top that, service was great, the whole team was attentive and we had an amazing view onto canary wharf.", "A definite YES to return sometime again!"]}
