{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r521288109", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "South East London's best restaurant", "diner_date": " August 2017", "rating_date": "5 September 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Philip1954", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "63"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "49"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r521288109-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["At last South East London has a restaurant to be proud of. The Peninsula at Greenwich is a class above. You now do not need to travel into Central London for a quality restaurant when there is one on your doorstep. The menu is not large but a good choice with two excellent fish options. Also the deserts are something to get the taste-buds following along with a great cheese selection. The service is very friendly and 5* something that does not always go hand in hand. This restaurant forms part of the Intercontinental Hotel at the O2. Therefore a cocktail at the Sky Bar is a must prior or after meal. Try to book a window seat if possible. The only minus for the whole evening were the side order of vegetable. They really were far too hard even for the connoisseurs. "]}
