{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r506264476", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Great normally disappointing on a Groupon deal!", "diner_date": " May 2017", "rating_date": "27 July 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "lcmlullabell", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r506264476-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["The meal was wonderful when we paid full price in January for my birthday. So we were really excited when there was a Groupon deal and went for my other half' s birthday , but were devastated and it spoilt our evening, when we had the meal as it was a cheaper version of the normal menu. So don't go for the deal, just go and pay full price, as the food is so beautiful normally. Expect to pay \u00a3200 including wine and you will love it, it is well worth it."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r503230800", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great Ideas and Even Better People", "diner_date": " July 2017", "rating_date": "18 July 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Karolina V", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "6"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r503230800-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["We dined at the Peninsula restaurant on the evening of 14th July, 2017. We chose this restaurant, funnily enough, for its location as the main purpose of our evening was to get as far away from central London as possible. Nonetheless, we chose this restaurant after seeing chef Tomas\u2019s work online and after reading numerous great reviews. I can confirm that we had one of our best dining our experiences in a very long time. My partner and I are into food and work within our industry ourselves so it is not as easy to impress us. However, chef Tomas and the sommelier Ucha, managed to do this without any doubt. It is visible throughout his food and ideas that Tomas is an experienced chef with new, unexpected ideas. He is also the one that can execute them very well. The sommelier, Ucha, seemed to have so much knowledge but was very interested to hear our thoughts. He could have acted like another know-it-all but he did not. Due to this we were able to develop an interesting conversation about food and wine. Other floor staff was very welcoming and greeted us warmly too. Definitely recommend visiting. We will be returning."]}
