{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r497945256", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Fine dining...quality food...amazing view...professional and friendly service...", "diner_date": " June 2017", "rating_date": "2 July 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Simone C", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "5"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r497945256-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["I had a dinner with friends here. ", "We were warmly welcome by Mirela (not sure about the name). ", "The table close to the windows. The view over the Thames and Canary Wharf is fantastic. ", "The warm friendly and professional service is unique. ", "You need to ask for Ucha: the wine expert.", "I was impressed about him. We asked him to advise which wine would be best for the dishes we ordered. When he was serving the wine he was explaining how it will taste and where the wine is from with the history of each wine. Ucha was incredible. The wines he served were actually the best suit for the food we had. ", "The food:you would think small portions as it is fine dining. You are wrong. I ate only a starter and a main and I was full same as my friends. The food was very good and I could say it was fresh. Well done to chefs as well for a great presentation.", "The dessert it was very tasty too. ", "Overall I was very very happy. I am planning to go back there next month with my girlfriend this time. I can promise Peninsula has a very romantic atmosphere too especially when sun goes down. I will go there again."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r496791842", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Great Dining", "diner_date": " June 2017", "rating_date": "28 June 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "anuradha2013", "reviewer_origin": ["Mumbai, India"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "384"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "572"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r496791842-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["It is on the water view drive, great view and even great food and service. Cool you heels and enjoy a leisurely meal."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r501272210", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "A fantastic tasting menu and more", "diner_date": " July 2017", "rating_date": "12 July 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Scourge-of-God", "reviewer_origin": ["Cambridge, England, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "66"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "18"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r501272210-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["Views:", "The photos do not do the restaurant justice. What are missing from the images are the amazing views of the Thames with its river traffic and the lights of the skyscrapers of Canary Warf at night on the other bank of the river. So expect spectacular views of near floor to ceiling windows. ", "Food: We were on a romantic getaway and invited a dear friend for a lovely evening of company in preparation for his hosting of us at the Henley Royal Regatta. I expected a excellent British cuisine inspired by Asian influences that keeps with the theme of the hotel. Our standards are high as we most recently experienced excellent cuisine at the restaurants of two other IC hotels in Canada. We were all overwhelmed by the works of art that can stand up to or surpass any Michelin rated restaurant. The key difference was the relaxed service and ambience of the Peninsula Restaurant. Being a new hotel, my expectations were staff who were new or less experienced. This was simply untrue as the experienced staff including Eva were led by the very experienced Associate Manager of the restaurant. Our evening went on and it will be one of the highlights of dinning experience. ", "Wine: Wine list is well selected and not overwhelming. Very affordable and rare vintages were mixed with more luxurious items. My partner was impressed by the available selection and the staff adjusted flawlessly to her being the decision maker for the wines. My friend was impressed with the Coravin wine pouring system that allowed the display and service from what must be a Nebuchadnezzar sized bottle. The associate manager was quick to point out this new technology and informed us of its wonders. ", "Service: a best mix of European and British. Seen but not heard mixed with convivial repartee when the service called for it. While we were not the only table in the uncrowded restaurant we felt as if we were at a Chef's table. Well Done. ", "We loved the restaurant so much that as a couple my partner and I decided to have the tasting menu the night before our departure from the hotel. We loved it and the portions were generous without being over indulgent and the art of the dishes that included a savory ice cream were on par with anything in Paris. ", "A nice hidden gem on the Thames waiting to be discovered by guests of the hotel or any gourmet."]}
