{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r464078016", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Just delightful", "diner_date": " March 2017", "rating_date": "2 March 2017", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "SaintsRFC", "reviewer_origin": ["Northampton, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "23"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "36"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r464078016-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["The food is truly exceptional, hats off to chef who produces some top quality dishes that taste amazing. Ate prior to a gig at the o2 and whilst staying in the Intercontinental Hotel. On the second floor of the hotel, looking out over the Thames to Canary Wharf - we had a corner table which took full advantage of the dual aspect floor to ceiling glass. The staff are knowledgeable and discrete and provide superb service - the whole place oozes class and quality. All the dishes we had (from the 3 course pre-show menu and great value I might add) were creative, flavoursome and looked amazing. If this place keeps delivering this type of food then accolades are sure to follow. Really really good - possibly one of the best I've eaten in. Well done!"]}
