{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r403005834", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Peaked with the starter!", "diner_date": " July 2016", "rating_date": "8 August 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "nibrika", "reviewer_origin": ["Marrakech, Morocco"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "141"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "122"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "50", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r403005834-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["Ate on a Friday night, was only 1 other couple when we arrived but few other tables later - lacked a bit of ambiance, however you really need a table by the window to make the most of the views so probably better that it is not too busy.", "We went for the tasting menu. Advertised as 5 courses but there is also amouse bouche and predessert.", "The starter of pea soup was brilliant - innovative presentation and flavours. This raised my expectations for the rest of the meal but, although the other courses were all well cooked and nice enough, they werent anything special and certainly not Michelen star level.", "Still we enjoyed the evening and service was very good."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r405371728", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "A newcomer with great promise", "diner_date": " July 2016", "rating_date": "14 August 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "GrantHodgkinson", "reviewer_origin": ["Welwyn, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "542"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "196"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r405371728-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["As we were staying at the hotel, we were keen to try Peninsula after drinks at the bar. Not wanting to over-indulge, we decided to do the fixed menu, which is accompanied by a class of champagne.", "In every aspect, our experience was incredible. Presentation is immaculate, perfectly complemented by flavours that inspire.", "This rivals several of the Michelin star establishments that are only a short ride west. Highly recommended.", "We'll be back, but for the tasting menu next time."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r423330972", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Amazing dinner!", "diner_date": " September 2016", "rating_date": "28 September 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "federicacI5774AE", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r423330972-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["Me and my boyfriend went to the Peninsula restaurant at the Intercontinental hotel in Greenwich on a quiet Tuesday evening for a romantic dinner, we went first for a cocktail in the skybar and then headed to the restaurant. We had an amazing tasting menu created by the brilliant head chef Tomas Lidakevicius, everything we had, from the canap\u00e9s to meat and fish were delicate and full of flavour. Desserts were the perfect end to this amazing meal with a butternut squash ice cream that blow our minds! Front of house staff was really kind and attentive, our waiter Ucha has been really helpful introducing us to every course we had and Rafaela was really friendly and professional. Overall a very nice night out in Greenwich! Highly recommended restaurant!!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r415309234", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Birthday Meal", "diner_date": " September 2016", "rating_date": "6 September 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Arnold L", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "171"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "92"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r415309234-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["We have visited the hotel a number of times but never used the restaurant. We had an early booking at 1900 and we arrived early for it so we used the cocktail bar on the 18 th floor. The hotel is a short walk from the 02 and North Greenwich station so good access for busses and tube. Car parking is expensive so avoid where possible. The restaurant and hotel ( Intercontinental ) is also accessible from North Greenwich Pier which has river bus access from Westminster and central London.", "The cocktail bar whilst quite expensive is worth a look, the views are great and as the evening sky far lens the lights of Canary Wharf and surroundings are quite spectacular. You either like city views or you don't but this is the best view close up of Canary Wharf that you can get.", "The restaurant was empty when we arrived and we had the pick of the tables, there are very few without a view and by t he time we left there was a party of 8 and t who other couples so it was not busy. I asked about the footfall and was t old honestly that unless their were conferences or functions or events at 02 then it can be quite. This suited us fine.", "We had gluten free options for my wife from t. He main menu and they were the best we / she has had in a restaurant. For mains we had the steak and I had the lamb and both were fantastic , cooked to perfection, presented superbly and tasted exactly as they should. I had the cheeseboard which was enough for two and we tried the semolina pudding for a gluten. / dairy free option. It was wonderful.", "I had a rose wine - the French option - we had a glass of ros\u00e9 champagne and one glass of port with the cheese. The bill was 200 pounds but the drinks to be fair were 40% of that so you can regulate. I would say you could get out under 100 with a drink each and using one of the fixed menus and that would be good value.", "The service was 100% - we were made to feel really very special - the explanations of the food was on par and we considered our evening worth every penny.", "We have booked to re visit and take the taster menu and see how that goes. All in all a great evening."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d10148721", "id_comment": "g186338-d10148721-r424988546", "resto": "Peninsula_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d10148721-Reviews-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Michelin Star material ", "diner_date": " October 2016", "rating_date": "4 October 2016", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "flr1987", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "5"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d10148721-r424988546-Peninsula_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["We visited the Peninsula Restaurant at the O2 Intercontinental last Saturday night, the restaurant was busy with most of the table occupied on our arrival at 8:30pm.", "The service was efficient, attentive without being intrusive. The view from the restaurant is impressive, the perfect background for a romantic dinner with partner or a business dinner.", "The highlight of the night though was the food, well presented and balanced. ", "I will be back soon for the inviting 7 course tasting menu..... (there is also a vegetarian option available, impressive!)"]}
